ğŸ“Œ How to use this Skript?  

This Skript allows you to create NPCs that, when clicked, make the player execute a command as if they had typed it themselves.  

ğŸ”¹ Create an NPC  
Use the command:  
`/pnj <NPC Name> <Command>`  
Example: `/pnj Shop shop`  
This will create an NPC named "Shop". When a player right-clicks it, they will automatically execute `/shop`.  

ğŸ”¹ Using NPCs  
- Right-clicking the NPC executes the command for the player.  
- Only players with the `admin.pnj` permission can modify or delete an NPC.  

ğŸ”¹ Edit an NPC  
- If an admin right-clicks an NPC while holding a name tag, they can rename it using the text on the tag.  
- If an admin right-clicks an NPC while holding bedrock, they can change its associated command.  

ğŸ”¹ Delete an NPC  
- An admin can delete an NPC by attacking it.  
- Other players cannot attack NPCs.  
